===Etymology===
{{AS.}} ''[[næs]]''; akin to {{Icel.}} ''[[nes]]'', {{Sw.}} ''[[näs]]'', {{Dan.}} ''[[næs]]'', {{E.}} [[Nose]]

===Noun===

'''ness'''
#{{geography}} A promontory; a cape; a headland. Ness is frequently used as a suffix in the names of places and promontories; as, Sheer''ness''  (''[[w:Ness (disambiguation)|See Wikipedia article for additional places.]]'').

